dc_title_s: Insurance maps of Hudson County, New Jersey : comprising West Hoboken, Town of Union, nearly all of Weehawken, and part of North Bergen : volume eight
dc_description_s: "2159." Includes title sheet, key, streets and specials index, key map, and text. Title in upper margin of sheets: West Hoboken. "West Hoboken was a municipality that existed in Hudson County, New Jersey, United States, from 1861 to 1925 ... On January 1, 1925, Union City was formed, replacing both Union Hill and West Hoboken."-- Wikipedia. Historic Maps copy has sheets 1-31 of Hudson County, N.J. series, showing West Hoboken; sheets 32-101 foldered separately.
